cff-version: 1.2.0
message: "If you use this dataset, code, or the Korean speech-level classifier, please cite the following."
title: "Korean Honorifics as a Prompt Variable: Speech-Level Effects on LLM Performance and Output Register"
abstract: >-
  Prompt politeness affects LLM performance in English, Chinese, and Japanese, yet Korean —
  a language with one of the most grammaticalized honorific systems — remained untested.
  This artifact systematically manipulates the six Korean speech levels as a prompt variable
  across three open-weight models (EXAONE 3.5, Qwen3, Llama 3.1) and three tasks, with
  113,400 model responses, a Kiwi-based speech-level classifier, and a full reproducible pipeline.
